The Trump Administration has released a strategic plan called "Charting a Course for Success: America's Strategy for STEM Education" to ensure that the United States remains a leader in scientific and technological innovation. The plan emphasizes the importance of lifelong access to high-quality education in science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM) for all Americans. It recognizes that STEM skills are crucial not only for economic prosperity and national security but also for success in various career paths and daily tasks that require knowledge of science and technology. The plan acknowledges the need to improve STEM education and training and promote diverse participation in STEM fields. It also calls for greater collaboration between educational institutions and employers to align educational paths with job opportunities. The plan was developed with input from various stakeholders and aims to guide efforts across the nation to improve STEM education and ensure the United States remains a global leader in STEM literacy, innovation, and employment.